<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idef9f79e7-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db" identifier="/us/usc/t54/s302505"><num value="302505">§ 302505.</num><heading> Eligibility and responsibility of certified local government</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Any local government—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idef9f79e8-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db" identifier="/us/usc/t54/s302505/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> that is certified under this chapter shall be eligible for funds under <ref href="/us/usc/t54/s302902/c/4">section 302902(c)(4) of this title</ref>; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idef9f79e9-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db" identifier="/us/usc/t54/s302505/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> that is certified, or making efforts to become certified, under this chapter shall carry out any responsibilities delegated to it in accordance with such terms and conditions as the Secretary considers necessary or advisable.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idef9f79ea-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db">(<ref href="/us/pl/113/287/s3">Pub. L. 113–287, § 3</ref>, <date date="2014-12-19">Dec. 19, 2014</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/128/3198">128 Stat. 3198</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
